===Etymology===
{{IPAchar|/arataɕiki/}} → {{IPAchar|/arataɕiĩ/}} → {{IPAchar|/arataɕiː/}}

{{ja-adj-shiku|新し|atarashi}}

In {{w|Old Japanese}}, the original term was read {{m|ja|新たし|tr=aratashi}}. By [[metathesis]] with {{m|ja|可惜し|tr=atarashi||[[precious]], [[regrettable]]}}, ''aratashi'' fell out of use in {{w|Middle Japanese}} and the "[[new]], [[modern]], [[fresh]]" senses assimilated into the latter ''atarashi''. {{rfv-etym|ja}}

